  "id": "PLACE_jurists_berth",
  "label": "Jurist's Berth",
  "description": "A compact sleeping cabin partitioned off The Iron-Straked Passage by a pitch-sealed hatch and iron-hasped frame. Tar-black planking and iron strapwork continue inside, with a bolted cot-box and a sea chest strapped to the bulkhead to withstand ramming shock. Along the inner lintel, registry stamps and a small jurisdiction plaque fix the berth within the ship’s licensed chain of access, while salt-caked warding nails are driven in a waist-high line around the walls. The air remains thick with tar, damp hemp, and bilge-salt, held close by minimal ventilation and shuttered scuppers.",
